        <div class="content">
            <h3><b>Diplomat pudding</b></h3>
            <ul>
                <li>Coarsely chop 100 g candied fruits.</li>
                <li>Put in a bowl with 75 g raisins and add 100 ml rum. Leave to macerate for 1 hour.</li>
                <li>Butter a 1.5 litre charlotte mould and sprinkle with icing sugar.</li>
                <li>Line the bottom with brioche slices and cover with a layer of the drained macerated fruit, reserving
                    the rum.</li>
                <li>Fill the mould in this way with alternate layers of bread and fruit.</li>
                <li>Beat 200 g caster sugar, 100 ml milk and 1 teaspoon vanilla sugar with 6 eggs and the rum in which
                    the fruit was macerated</li>
                <li>Gradually pour this mixture into the mould, allowing the brioche to soak up the liquid.</li>
                <li>Cook for 1 hour in a bain marie in a pre-heated oven at 150 degrees celsius, make sure the liquid in
                    the bain marie does not come to a boil.</li>
                <li>Allow to cool completely, remove from the mould and serve with crystallized fruit.</li>

